messages.message:
On a day to day, I think a shopping list or list of 10 songs, I probably thought it would be a 1D array! 

Are the two separated because table uses table extractor and list uses a different method? I noticed that if I had a bank statement with tables split across 2 pages, using the list type gave me all the records spread between two pages, and table gave me only the first or second table, but not both

Tables are meant to extract things that visually look like tables. List is meant for extracting things that appear more than once in the document (e.g. list of rental properties). We are considering changing the copy to something like "Multiple Items", so it's clear that we're not looking for a visual list (aka 1D array) in the document, but rather looking for all occurrences of the field name
